#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.44:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.44:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.44:0.3"
msgid "44. Kūṭāgārasutta"
msgstr "44. A Bungalow"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: hi, bhikkhave → yo ca kho bhikkhave (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.44:1.1"
msgid "“Yo hi, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose someone were to say:"

msgctxt "sn56.44:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ anabhisamecca … pe … "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ anabhisamecca sammā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Without truly comprehending the noble truths of suffering, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the path, I will completely make an end of suffering.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:1.3"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is not possible."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.44:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "It’s as if someone were to say:"

# BB has “will erect” for aropessami. But this seems to rely on a meaning of the word that is only attested in later texts. (PTS dict has SN.iii.12 for this sense, but this is wrong; there it means “refute”.)
msgctxt "sn56.44:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kūṭāgārassa heṭṭhimaṃ gharaṃ akaritvā uparimaṃ gharaṃ āropessāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Before the lower story of a bungalow is built, I will climb up to the upper "
"story.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:2.3"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati;"
msgstr "That is not possible."

msgctxt "sn56.44:2.4"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "In the same way, suppose someone were to say:"

msgctxt "sn56.44:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ anabhisamecca … pe … "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ anabhisamecca sammā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Without truly comprehending the noble truths of suffering, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the path, I will completely make an end of suffering.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:2.6"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is not possible."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.44:3.1"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "But suppose someone were to say:"

msgctxt "sn56.44:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisamecca … pe … "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisamecca sammā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘After truly comprehending the noble truths of suffering, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the path, I will completely make an end of suffering.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:3.3"
msgid "ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is possible."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.44:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "It’s as if someone were to say:"

msgctxt "sn56.44:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kūṭāgārassa heṭṭhimaṃ gharaṃ karitvā uparimaṃ gharaṃ āropessāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘After the lower story of a bungalow is built, I will climb up to the upper "
"story.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:4.3"
msgid "ṭhānametaṃ vijjati;"
msgstr "That is possible."

msgctxt "sn56.44:4.4"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "In the same way, suppose someone were to say:"

msgctxt "sn56.44:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisamecca … pe … "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisamecca sammā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘After truly comprehending the noble truths of suffering, its origin, its "
"cessation, and the path, I will completely make an end of suffering.’"

msgctxt "sn56.44:4.6"
msgid "ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is possible."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.453"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.44:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.44:5.2"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
